3. e4{ Obviously this is consistent with  f7 - f5 . Black wants to keep the center closed to avoid running into problems since he pushed his f-pawn, and he takes advantage of having better control of the  e4 -square. I still think White should be better here, but if Black wants a plan with  f7 - f5  and meeting  d2 - d4  with  e5 - e4 , this is definitely his best moment to do so. }( 3...d6 4.Nc3 Be7 5.Bh3 { Transposes to the 2...  Be7   line  in chapter 1. } )
4. Nc3{ As always, our knight goes to  c3 . }
