10. O-O( { We should be patient and not take back on  d3  just yet. }10.exd3?! Nxd5!= { I dislike allowing this option. I want Black to have to worsen his structure when he takes back on  d5 . } )
10. cxd5{ This is a sad necessity for Black. He must accept an isolated pawn as well. }
11. exd3{ Now and only now, we take the pawn back. }
11. Nc6
12. Nc3
12. Qa5{ This position has been seen a few times, and Black is almost equalizing. Still, I think I can put him under some pressure. }
13. Re1+{ This is not only the best move, but it also invites a natural mistake. }
13. Be7{ This has been the only move played so far. Now, White can be very energetic. }
14. b4{ It turns out not to be so easy to take this pawn! White gets ready to fianchetto his other bishop. }
14. Qxb4( 14...axb3 15.Bb2⩲ { Black cannot take on  a2 , and next up we will play  Nd2xb3  followed by  Nc3 - e2 . Black is under some pressure thanks to White's more active pieces. } )
15. Nxd5
15. Nxd5
16. Bxd5{  Ra1 - b1  comes next, and Black is under unpleasant pressure thanks to White's active pieces. }
