3. h6{ This move might look a little weird, but Black has a point. He makes a patient waiting move, asking us to make up our minds. If we play  Ng1 - f3 , then after  e5 - e4  and  d7 - d5 , Black is claiming that  h7 - h6  is more useful than  c7 - c6  would be. And, by not committing his knight to  c6  so soon, he is pointing out that we should be less inclined to bring our own knight to  c3 , as then  Bf8 - b4  would be possible without running into  Nc3 - d5 . Still, it feels a little too retro to me for Black to be able to move his h-pawn instead of fighting for the center and still manage to equalize. }
4. Nf3{ I like falling into Black's trap. We approach the position the same way we would if he had played  c7 - c6  instead. }
