2. h5{ This move always feels a bit weird to me, but whenever we push  g2 - g3 , it is always something we should consider and be ready for. Indeed, Nihal played it against me in the Banter Blitz Cup - I somehow doubt he would have done the same in a classical game, but it was not so easy to disarm in fast time controls. }
3. Nf3{ I like this direct move the most. White stops  h5 - h4  at the source and hits the  e5 -pawn. }
3. Nc6{ This is probably Black's best move, but it is also a very bad sign for him. If he is unable to challenge the  f3 -knight and get  h5 - h4  through,  h7 - h5  can't really be justified. }
4. Nc3{ White stops  e5 - e4 , and we are ready for  d2 - d4  next, attacking in the center in response to a thrust on the flank. }
