8. d6{ Otherwise White might even put the bishop on  d6 . }
9. bxc6
9. bxc6
10. d3{ Now, the last pitfall to avoid is that continuing with  Ng1 - f3  will blunder a piece to  e5 - e4 . So, we will need to play  Qd1 - d2  first, but then  Ng1 - f3  and  O-O  will follow. }
