6. e4{ White prevents  d7 - d5  at the source. }
6. O-O
7. Nge2
7. Na6{ Black can also try this move, aiming for  Nc7  next and playing  d7 - d5  in one move. It looks a bit artificial to me, and White should be better. }
8. Be3{ I like this move better than castling. White should be aiming to push  d2 - d4  as soon as possible, and I want to be ready to take back with the bishop. }
8. Nc7
9. d4{ White wins the race to the central break and Black is in big trouble. }
9. d5( { This is the only way for Black to fight back, but blowing up the center will not save him either. }9...d6?! { I would expect a human to accept a passive position with a move like this one. }10.Qd2± { With  O-O  and  Ra1 - d1  coming next, White is obviously better thanks to his extra space. } )
10. cxd5
10. cxd5
11. dxe5
11. Bxe5( 11...dxe4 12.Bc5! { Black has a hard time defending against the direct threats. White's pieces are so much more active and menacing than their black counterparts } )
12. exd5{ A pawn is a pawn. }
