8. Ba7{ This is Black's most common move. It makes a lot of sense given that he played  a7 - a6  last move. Now,  d2 - d4  would play right into his hands with  Bc8 - g4  coming next. We should be more patient. }
9. h3{ I like this move a lot. White keeps the bishop off of  g4 , and he can hope for  d2 - d4  to come next. Once this happens, I think Black will be best advised to exchange pawns. Then, we will be happy to have not put our bishop on  b2 , as it will sit better on  e3 . }
9. Re8
10. d4{ Now, I think Black is best advised to take on  d4 . We are ready to take on  e5  next. }
10. exd4
11. Nxd4{ I like opening up the long diagonal. Now, Black should definitely take on  d4  to avoid getting a horrible structure. }
11. Nxd4
12. exd4
12. c6
13. d5{ Black is in a tough spot. Advancing  c6 - c5  will bury his  a7 -bishop, bit it's no fun to end up with an isolani on  d6  either. }
