[Result "*"]

1. c4
1. e5
2. g3
2. c6{ With Black's second move of the game, he intends to immediately fight for the center of the board with  d7 - d5  next. The position transfers into a reversed Alapin, where White gets the free move  g2 - g3 . This tempo totally changes the character of the position. }
3. Nf3{ In the proper Alapin, I always preferred 2...  Nf6  to 2...  d5 , and when playing White in a similar position, I share the same preference. }
3. d6{ One does not play 2...  c6  to immediately give up on pushing  d7 - d5  on the very next move. }
4. Nc3{ White takes control of the  e4 -square. If he is allowed to advance  d2 - d4  next, he obviously will have a fantastic position. }
4. Nf6
5. Bg2
5. Be7
6. O-O
6. O-O
7. Qc2{ White has other good moves, but I like this one for its simplicity. White takes control of the  e4 -square, and he is ready for  d2 - d4  to come next. Black is definitely a bit worse. }
