3. e4{ I really don't see Black playing anything else. }
4. Nd4{ Now, it is important for Black to realize that he is not simply playing a reversed Alapin. The extra tempo is huge for White! Being able to get the bishop to  g2  without any kind of disaster striking on  f2  means that White will have a much safer king than in a normal mainline Alapin, and he also will have a much easier time pressuring the  e4 -pawn. }
4. d5( 4...Nf6 5.Bg2 { Transposes to the next chapter. } )
5. cxd5
5. cxd5{ I could easily see a human making this overly ambitious decision. After all, what could be more natural than capturing towards the center and trying to bolster the  e4 -pawn, which is the source of a nice space advantage? }
6. d3
6. Nf6
7. Bg2{ White has an incredibly simple plan. Castle and  Nc3 . Black will have a very hard time holding the center together. }
7. Bc5
8. Nb3
