12. hxg4{ Now, if Black is given time to get his pieces out, he will be much better. He will have more space in the center, our king is sketchy, and we have weak pawns. We need to maximize the lead in development, and the plan is to bring the queen to  b3  next. }
12. hxg3{ Of course, this is Black's most natural move. Now, there is no time to waste. }
13. Qb3{ We do not care about the pawn on  f2 . All that matters is developing as fast as possible. It is a bad sign for Black that the computer insists he must take on  c3  here. }
