7. Nc3{ As always, our knight goes to  c3 . Now, White actually has a devilish idea to push  b2 - b4  next. }
7. h6{ This is Black's best move, and a very tough one to make. The point is prophylaxis against  b2 - b4 , which now can be met with  e5 - e4  without allowing the knight to come to  g5 . }
8. d3
8. Bd6
9. b3{ White has other good moves, but this seems easiest to me. }
9. O-O
10. Bb2{ The computer does not mind Black's position so much here, but it still does give White some nagging edge. I like that we can plan a normal plan with  Rc1  and  Na4  to pressure the c-file, and I'm not sure what Black is hoping to accomplish in the meantime. }
