8. exd4
9. Nb5{ White will take back his lost pawn on  d4 , and Black will have a very hard time keeping the position under control. Still, there are some important lines to memorize. }
9. Bc5
10. Qc2{ The bishop is kicked away, and  Rf1 - d1  follows next. Black is in big trouble. }
10. Bc4( 10...Be7 11.Rd1!+- { White will take on  d4  next, and Black is already done for. } )
11. Bf4{ The loose bishop on  c4  means that Black cannot play the generally desirable move  Nb6 - d5 . He is facing massive concrete issues. }
